# ComfyUI RMBG

Three modes share one script. It writes outputs under the media library and prints `OUTPUT /absolute/path/output.png`.

## Modes

### `rmbg` (default) — basic background removal

Standard ComfyUI RMBG/rembg semantic background removal. Default for any plain "remove background / 抠图 / transparent PNG" request without further qualification.

```bash
python3 skills/comfyui-rmbg/scripts/comfyui_rmbg.py --image /path/to/input.jpg
```

### `ermbg` — smart matting (for AI-generated assets)

Use when the user says **智能抠图 / AI生图抠图 / smart matte / ERMBG**, or when the source is an AI-generated asset (绿幕图 / 白底卡通 / 已经抠脏的 RGBA / 多个独立小物体). Routes per image and outputs both clean RGB foreground and a properly inverted alpha channel via the ERMBG custom node.

```bash
python3 skills/comfyui-rmbg/scripts/comfyui_rmbg.py --mode ermbg --image /path/to/input.png
# shortcut: --smart
```

ermbg-only options (all auto by default):

```bash
--despill {auto,unmix,chroma_cap,local_borrow,closed_form,none}
--use-keyer {auto,on,off}
--bg-color "0,200,0"          # composite color for re-matting dirty RGBA
--matting-model "ZhengPeng7/BiRefNet-matting"
```

When to pick `ermbg` over plain `rmbg`:
- Input came from AI generation (especially with a known/specified background color).
- Multiple independent subjects in one image (basic RMBG drops the small ones).
- White-background hard-edged graphic / logo (basic RMBG leaves white halo on dark composites).
- An RGBA the user is unhappy with — let ermbg auto-detect it as dirty and re-matte.

### `edge-wand` — Photoshop-like magic wand

Use when the user says to remove only the surrounding same-color background, preserve enclosed same-color holes/areas, or avoid removing same-colored regions inside the subject. Removes only pixels connected to the image edges.

```bash
python3 skills/comfyui-rmbg/scripts/comfyui_rmbg.py --mode edge-wand --image /path/to/input.jpg --tolerance 24
# shortcut: --edge-wand
```

## Rules

- Return the printed output path and render the PNG when useful.
- Keep generated cutouts in `/Users/ethanhu/.openclaw/media/openclaw-production/images/rmbg/` unless the user asks for another destination.
- Do not install models, download model files, or modify the ComfyUI server from this skill. Missing nodes/models are server configuration problems; report the exact script error.
- For advanced options, run `python3 skills/comfyui-rmbg/scripts/comfyui_rmbg.py --help`.
